Capture and hold as many control points as you can
Hold over half the points to bleed the enemy's tickets
Getting kills also makes the enemy team lose a ticket
You win by reducing the enemy team's tickets to 0
Capture points faster with more players inside the circle
Place chemicals near control points to defend them better
Hold ({{%01%}}) to change teams up the top left of the screen
This level is ahead of your current progress in the campaign. There will be spoilers!
Explore the map to discover hidden unlocks
Focus on kill streaks to earn extra cash
Experience gained from awards is used to unlock items in the ITEMS page.
The size of the rewards depend on the duration and number of players in the server.
you have not logged in and aren't eligible for any awards
clan with the highest average score per minute
all players who completed the speedrun

This will finish your survival run and you'll miss the end of round XP bonuses.
Are you sure you want to leave this party?
Are you sure you want to quit?
Are you ready to kick some robo-ass?

Your character will wear a plate of bronze shoulder armor and look brilliantly badass.
Your character will wear a plate of silver shoulder armor and look super sexy.
Your character will wear a plate of golden shoulder armor and look genuinely gorgeous.
Your character will wear a plate of ruby shoulder armor and look radically radiant.
Your character will wear a plate of diamond shoulder armor and look dashingly dangerous.
Your character will wear a plate of amethyst shoulder armor and look absolutely amazing.
When you fall from the sky you will leave behind a colorful trail of smoke.
Whenever you kill an enemy with your knife a booming HUMILIATION voice-over will play to everyone in the server.
target: Bıçağınızla her düşman öldürdüğünüzde yüksek bir HUMILIATION sesi sunucudaki herkesin duyabileceği şekilde oynar. Sunucu herkese rakibinizi ustalıkla bıçakladığınız mesajını yollar.

source: Makes your knife glow in the dark. Give your enemies something shiny to look at before you stab them in the gut.
target: Bıçağınız parlak ve renkli ışıklar saçar. Düşmanlarınızı boğazlamadan önce bakacak parlak bir şey vermiş olun.

source: This will reskin your knife to look like a baseball bat. Killing an enemy with the baseball bat will knock his head off and send it flying into the distance. This doesn't affect gameplay.
target: Bıçağınızı bir beyzbol sopasına dönüştürür!  Düşmanınızı beyzbol sopasıyla öldürünce kafasını boynundan koparır ve uzaklara uçurur. Unutmayın ki sopanın oyun içindeki davranışı bıçakla fark göstermez.

source: This will reskin your knife to look like a lightsaber. Killing an enemy with the lightsaber will emit a massive burst of energy and slice your opponent into itty bitty little pieces. This doesn't affect gameplay.
Unleash your inner Rambo with this sweet bandana. The bandana will trail behind you as you run around with cool cloth dynamics.
The cape is like the bandana but more stylish. You'll look like a superhero as you jump down upon your unsuspecting victims.
Activates neons lights under your vehicle. Mix and match with your headlights to created a groovy disco drift.
Lets you change the colour of the light emmitted when you fire your gun.
Lets you change the color of your vehicle's headlights. Use the slider below to set the color.
Burn rubber with some sweet decals on your vehicle. Flames, flowers, stripes, you name it. The decals are painted onto your vehicle in a color of your choosing.
Change the color of your bullet trails. Your enemies will know they're in trouble when they see your uniquely colored bullets fly at them from across the map.
If you own the Deluxe Edition DLC this medallion will show next to your name. You'll also show off your account level when you win a BR round.
Upgrades the Supporter medallion shown next to your name. This only applies if you own the Deluxe Edition DLC.
Changes the appearance of your headgear.
Gives you spooky spiky horns when you're a zombie.
When you start a match you can select this Genome to play with special bonuses (NOTE: This feature will be added in a future version)
As a mercenary guards have no effect on missions. You must only target other mutants.
This mission requires teammates and does not work as a mercenary.
Creates a buy zone where you're standing. Chemicals in this buy zone will be discounted.
Used to capture Conquest control points. Place this directly onto a control point to capture it.
Creates a supply drop at your current location.
Teleports you to other Warp Fields (you need at least 2). Stand in it, hold ALT, and click an arrow to teleport.
Reveals enemies within {{%01%}} meters of it.
Allows you to capture enemy chemicals by standing on top of them.

Protects your chemicals from enemy Neutralizers. Place this on a chemical and if an enemy tries to neutralize it, it will remove the Insulator but save the original chemical. Can only be used once per chemical.
Reveals the location of nearby enemy chemicals making them easier to neutralize. The revealing range is
Upgrade: Makes the chemical you're standing in invisible to enemies unless they stand inside it.
Enemies in your Goo Trap are slowed for {{%01%}} seconds.
Creates a laser that zaps enemies who walk through it. This deals {{%01%}} of their current health.
Explodes for {{%01%}} hp damage when an enemy steps inside it.
Extends your magazine by giving a free bullet every {{%01%}} shots.
Your bullets slow civs and cops by {{%01%}} for {{%02%}}.
Your gun's critical damage will increase by {{%01%}} when you kill an enemy player or a cop. This can go {{%02%}} higher than the default cap of {{%03%}}.
This is placed into the map and is hidden from enemies unless they stand inside it.
Does not work as a zombie.
You will gain {{%01%}} health per second for every point in the Physical tree.
You will regenerate shifts {{%01%}}% faster for every point in the Mental tree.
You will deal {{%01%}}% more bullet damage for every point in the Cybernetic tree.
You can take a skill up to level 3 once you've spent {{%01%}} points in its skill tree.
Whenever you kill an enemy they'll leave a puddle of blood on the ground that damages other enemies who step in it.
Increases the cash and health you gain from killing enemy players and cops. This increases further based on your wanted level. By default, player kills give +{{%01%}} health.
Allows you to shoot out the window of your car while driving (with worse accuracy). Also continuously restores the health of the vehicle.
Makes you jump higher when standing in your chemicals. Also makes your chemicals restore charges faster.
Spawns grenades that spin around you. These grenades will be randomly tossed at nearby enemies over time.
Whenever you fall onto the ground near an enemy you will reduce their rate of fire. Enemies killed in this state will drop a heart piece on death.
Restores health by a percentage of the damage you deal to enemies.
Makes you heal faster when out of combat. By default players heal at {{%01%}} hp/s after {{%02%}}s.
Creates a shield that blocks enemy bullets.
Makes you invisible as long as you don't stand too close to an enemy player or cop.
Slows the speed of all bullets in a circle around you. Any bullets you fire within Bullet Time will steer towards enemies.
Increases your rate of fire. This also applies to nearby allies when you cast it.
Creates deadly blades that spin around you and slash nearby enemies. After a short time these blades will bursts out to deal damage at range.
Shocks all enemy players and bullets in front of you. Shocking an enemy will make their bullets travel slower. Also, bullets hit by your Shockwave will be frozen in mid-air.
Launches a long range nuke that creates a large radioactive field. Enemies that step into this take damage over time, and take additional damage if hit by the initial blast.
Fires a poison dart that deals damage over time. This damage can't kill enemy players, but can reduce them to 1hp.
Launches an explosive ball of plasma that gains damage the further it travels.
Creates a shield around you whenever you cast a skill. This will briefly protect you from enemy weapon damage.
Your bullets will briefly deal extra damage after shifting. This does not apply when you shift without charges and lose health.
Makes you move faster by drifting on air. Your weapons also have no movement slowdown while drifting. Use a shift to stop drifting.
Bounces bullets off your Force Field. Also causes your Force Field to deal damage to nearby enemies when it explodes.
Creates a spinning vortex on the ground that slows enemies. You will steal health from each enemy caught inside it.
Increases your bullet speed and range.
Improves the speed that you can reload and swap between weapons.
Lets you see through walls by revealing nearby enemies and loot crates. Also briefly reveals enemies after you damage them.
Makes your bullets bounce off walls.
Slows the movement speed of all enemies within your radiation field.
Throws a line of spikes onto the ground that damage enemies who walk across it.
Fires additional balls when you cast Plasma Ball. These extra balls do reduced damage.

Whenever you are damaged by an enemy, Counter Spell will automatically trigger and reduce that incoming damage. It provides extra strong protection against non-bullet damage. After triggering it must recharge.
Throws a smoke bomb on the ground that instantly makes you invisible. You will remain invisible as long as you stay inside the smoke.
Steals enemy bullets and seeks them back towards your enemies. This occurs when you toggle off Bullet Time.
When Frenzy is active, each bullet you fire has a chance to not reduce your ammo, extending your magazine size.
Marks your position with an X on the ground. After a short time (or when you cast again) you'll teleport back to this location and restore lost health.
Speeds up your skill cooldowns whenever you get a kill. The reduction is a percentage of the remaining cooldown time.
You'll gain health based on a percentage of the damage you deal with parasites.
Infected enemies will take increased weapon damage. They will also leave a trail on the ground that infects other enemies, applying Venom to them as well.
Summons an orb that increases the damage of your bullets when they fly through it. Does not work when you stand within it.
Fires a stream of parasites that bounce off walls and penetrate through enemies. Briefly disables your weapons.
Creates a clone of you that confuses enemies. This clone will move towards your target. It will shoot, but not do any damage.
Increases the damage of all your skills. Also whenever you cast a skill, the next bullet you shoot with be enchanted with extra damage.
Pretty awful as a car. But it's cheap and makes a nice step for jumping over walls.
target: Vasıta olarak berbat ancak ucuz ve duvarları turmanmak için iyi bir basamak görevi görür.

source: Fast and agile - just watch out for the low health. If it catches on fire you'll burn.
Fast and durable - a great all-rounder. Can survive a direct shot from a Bazooka.
A good combat vehicle great for co-op drivebys. Press [F3] to hop into the back and shoot.
Has a radar that sees through walls and reveals the location of nearby enemies.
Very durable for its price and with 6 seats it's great for transporting your squad.
Fastest car in the game. Hold [SHIFT] to boost and scoop up all the loot in the map.
Comes with a ticking time bomb. [LEFT CLICK] to toggle the timer on and off.
A huge truck with massive health and 5 passenger seats. The back 3 seats allow for drivebys.
target: Çok canı ve 5 yan koltuğu olan kocaman bir kamyon. Arkadaki 3 koltuğu tam 360 derece bir ateş alanı yaratır. Çok pahalı ama dostlar ile sen nerdeyse durdurulamazsın!

source: Fires 2 homing missiles that deal extra damage against vehicles. [LEFT CLICK] to fire.
Drive the Extraction Truck to its extraction zone.
[LEFT CLICK] to fire a smoking hot Flamethrower. The Cybertruck's windows are shatterproof.
[LEFT CLICK] to turn on the siren and scare off gangsters up to no good.
Silent and deadly. Great for finishing enemies off at close range.
Kaboom! Deals more damage the closer it lands to your enemies.
Explodes with a huge flash of light that blinds nearby enemies.
Fires a homing missile that deals huge damage against vehicles.
A silenced pistol with a fast switch time. Unlike other guns, you won't be revealed when firing it.
target: Güzel keskin susturuculu bir tabanca. Ateş ettiğinde yakındaki muhafızlar duymaz.

source: High damage makes this a great sidearm. Does extra damage vs civs and cops.
An extremely mobile superweapon that fires bullets that slow civs and cops.
A great run & gun weapon with the fastest movement speed in the game.
A high rof and high movement speed make this a great all-round weapon.
A high damage superweapon. Its bullets pierce through enemies.
Does huge damage at point blank range.
An auto-shotgun with huge close range DPS.
A powerful superweapon that fires explosive bullets. Hold the fire button to charge an extra powerful blast.
Very effective at range, but you'll need to burst fire to control its recoil.
Accurate and great at range. Fires in short bursts of 3.
An extremely accurate superweapon that fires seeking bullets.
Has a huge clip size and deals extra vehicle damage.
Fires long range bullets and deals extra vehicle damage.
An extremely high damage superweapon that deals extra damage against vehicles.
A sniper with an extended scope lets you see enemies further away.
Fires extremely fast bullets and with a scope for long range sniping.
A deadly superweapon that fires a beam of photons. Its bullets pierce through enemies.
Tosses a flaming bottle that explodes on impact.
Fires a flare that explodes on impact. Good for shooting enemies behind cover.
An extremely deadly superweapon that shoots fire and sets cars on fire.
Aww man, you got blood on my shirt.
Nearby allies support you by slowly regenerating your mana and health.
target: Yakındaki dostlarınız sizin büyünüzü ve canınızı artırarak yardım ediyorlar.

source: Left click skills to add them. Right click to view them.
Click 'Start Adding Skills' to create a skill build.
If you die you become a zombie. But you can revive by killing a survivor (in red) or winning the heart crate.
Press ({{%01%}}) to chat. Say 'wassup' to receive a bonus 10xp!
Welcome mutant! To win you'll need to become more powerful. Kill an enemy to get cash and XP.
Grenades are very powerful. Buy some and then blow up a civilian. Throw nades with middle mouse or ({{%01%}}).
Enter a car with ({{%01%}}), then kill a cop. You can shoot out the window when your car isn't moving.
Hold ({{%01%}}) and click 'Reset Skill Build' from the drop-down skills menu up the top of the screen.
Leveling up gives you skill points. Hold ({{%01%}}) and spend a skill point on FORCE FIELD.
Active skills are shown above your health bar. Press ({{%01%}}) to cast Force Field. This can be cast every 20s.
This is the Outbreak game mode. To win you need to kill zombies, collect their souls and return them to the bomb.
After collecting souls you need to return them to the bomb. Follow the arrow on your screen to take your souls to the bomb. Hold (TAB) to see scores.
target: Ruh topladıkdan sonra bombaya geri getirmeniz gerekiyor. Her ruh karşılığında skor, para, büyü, can ve deneyim kazanıcaksınız. Ekranınızdaki oku takip edip bombaya geri getirin. (TAB)'a basılı tutarak skorunuzu görün.

source: Under the minimap you'll see a 'Kill Contract'. This increases over time and is awarded to you on your next kill.
Escape the blue circle in the minimap. Press {{%01%}} to toggle map zoom. Don't damage a cop or the circle will reset!
Try different vendors until you see the FISSION MINE chemical, then buy it. When carrying this you'll passively get free grenades.
Place your 'Fission Mine' in a busy area by holding ({{%01%}}). This makes a hidden bomb that will detonate when enemies step in it.
Stand inside your shop and buy something. You can place shops as long as you have charges.
Pick up your chemical by standing in it and pressing ({{%01%}}).
In Conquest you need to capture all of the Control Points in the map.
Capture a point by standing next to it. The more allies nearby, the faster you will capture.
This is the Extraction game mode. Follow the white arrow on your screen to capture the enemy flag.
Follow the arrow and take the flag to the enemy flag near your spawn. Hold (TAB) to see scores.
This is the Checkpoint game mode. To win you need do laps with the Battery in a vehicle. Grab a car, then follow the white arrow on your screen to pick up the Battery.
Follow the white arrow on your screen to drive the battery through each of the checkpoints. Hold (TAB) to see scores.
Stand inside an enemy chemical, hold ({{%01%}}), and select 'Neutralize Chemicals' to destroy it.
Press (F10) to finish this tutorial. This opens the How to Play Guide if you want to learn more.
Win round one to get bonus XP and cash. The player count is shown above the minimap.
Search for a civilian with yellow text above him. Then hold ({{%01%}}) and buy an MP5 (a tier 2 gun).
Right Click ({{%01%}}) to shift. Shift charges restore over time.
Shifts briefly increase your damage (shown in purple). Kill a civilian with critical bullets by shifting just before you shoot.
A full game has 4 rounds, but you only need to win the FINAL round. Use earlier rounds to level up and prepare for the final showdown!
XP is now enabled. Get kills until you level up. Your level is shown next to the health bar.
Follow the mission arrow to find a civilian with a green text bubble above his head, then press ({{%01%}}).
Missions are shown above the minimap. Do them to level up faster than your enemies! For this mission you need to kill 6 cops.
Learn to play and earn bonus XP!
The player count, timer, and your score are shown here.
Your health, lives and shifts are shown down here.
Press Q to switch weapons, and middle mouse to throw grenades.
Press 1, 2, 3 to cast skills. Hold ALT to spend skill points.
to toggle this guide on and off.

The meaning of life, the universe and everything you need to know about Geneshift can be found in this guide; so toggle this back on when you're ready to play like a pro. Until then you can press ENTER to chat with the server and ask questions. Have fun!
I JUST WANT TO STOP DYING!!
EARN A LITTLE EXTRA ON THE SIDE..
What do I have to do?
Follow the arrow on your screen to reach the next checkpoint. Try to earn combo kills to gain extra cash.
What if I miss some text?
Press (ENTER) to bring up the chat log. The green lines have important tips. Also when playing singleplayer you can hold (ALT) to pause the game and read the text at your own pace.
Stay out of combat for a few seconds to trigger auto-heal. Use vehicles for protection while looting. Unlock healing skills with (ALT). Buy expensive weapons to deal extra damage.
target: Kendini iyileştirmek için kısa bir süre boyunca mücadeleden uzak dur. Yuvarlar kontrol noktaların içinde iken silah satın al (B). Son olarak, İyileştirme yetenekleri aç (ALT) ve Sağ Tık, C ve Z'ye basarak kullan.

source: To win, simply be the last man standing on the final round. The best way to do this is to earn cash and XP in the earlier rounds to become as strong as possible.
Kill civilians and players to earn cash and XP. Unlock healing skills and buy a tier 2 gun as soon as possible. If you become a zombie, head towards a heart crate to try revive.

When you view the skills page through the main menu you're looking at your permanent skill build. This build is only used in permanent multiplayer servers and persists between rounds. This build is not used in quickmatches or the campaign.
DLC owners can host their own legacy game modes and play against bots. To play against humans it's better to join an official server.
Customize your skill draft with the buttons down the bottom right.

TIP: Try enabling skills that work well together and disable the rest. EG: Create a 'Sniper' build with long ranged skills only, like Energize and Plasma Ball. This way you only see relevant skills in-game.
Basic accounts can only save {{%01%}} builds at a time. Delete an existing build, or get the DLC to create as many builds as you want!
You can improve your FPS by updating your graphics drivers. For now, would you like Geneshift to optimise your graphics settings?
